<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="341" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,259,934]" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,763,789]" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">Description</emphasis>
(
<specimenCount box="[353,439,763,790]" pageId="40" pageNumber="341" type="male">5 males</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[492,599,763,789]" pageId="40" pageNumber="341" type="female">3 females</specimenCount>
measured). Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[886,968,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–95" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1747,1771]" captionTargetBox="[174,1411,469,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-151@38.[158,1429,453,1724]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 94–95. Trichotichnus hamulipenis sp. n., habitus. 94, nominotypical subspecies (above Bapo); 95, T. hamulipenis nepalensis ssp. n. (holotype). Scale bar = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6781755" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6781755/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">Fig. 94</figureCitation>
. On average, body larger (length 9.0– 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" pageId="40" pageNumber="341" unit="mm" value="10.5">10.5 mm</quantity>
, mean 10.0 mm), elytra relatively wider and shorter (EL/EW 1.43–1.54, mean 1.47, and EL/PL 2.59–2.80, mean 2.77), pronotum in central portion very finely punctate or almost impunctate, elytral preapical sinuation (
<figureCitation box="[1345,1428,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 96–97" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1168,1192]" captionTargetBox="[153,1425,777,1137]" captionTargetId="figure-266@39.[153,1434,777,1145]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 96–97. Trichotichnus hamulipenis sp. n., elytral apex. 96, nominotypical subspecies; 97, T. hamulipenis nepalensis ssp. n. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6781757" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6781757/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">Fig. 96</figureCitation>
) in most specimens slightly shallower and internal sac of aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[903,999,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 98–105" captionStartId="40.[151,264,1637,1661]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,964,1605]" captionTargetId="figure-323@40.[151,1436,957,1614]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURES 98–105. Trichotichnus hamulipenis sp. n.: 98–102, nominotypical subspecies (98–100, holotype; 101 &amp; 102, Cikai); 103–105, T. hamulipenis nepalensis ssp. n. (holotype). 98 &amp; 103, terminal lamella of aedeagus; 99, 100, 104 &amp; 105, median lobe of aedeagus; 101, gonocoxite; 102, laterotergite, gonosubcoxite, and gonocoxite. Dorsal (98, 100, 103 &amp; 105), lateral (99, 101 &amp; 104) and ventral (102) views. a, apical spiny patch. Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm (98, 101–103), B = 1.0 mm (99, 100, 104 &amp; 105)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6781759" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6781759/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">Fig. 100</figureCitation>
) without distinct curved spiny patch in apical portion near apical spine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6781759" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6781759" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6781759/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="341" startId="40.[151,264,1637,1661]" targetBox="[158,1430,964,1605]" targetPageId="40">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,1637,1770]" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,352,1637,1661]" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">FIGURES 98–105.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Kataev &amp; Hongbin &amp; Wrase, 2022" authorityName="Kataev &amp; Hongbin &amp; Wrase" authorityYear="2022" box="[357,625,1637,1661]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trichotichnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamulipenis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[357,625,1637,1661]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">Trichotichnus hamulipenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[630,686,1638,1662]" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[630,686,1638,1662]" pageId="40" pageNumber="341" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
: 98–102, nominotypical subspecies (98–100, holotype; 101 &amp; 102, Cikai); 103–105, 
<taxonomicName box="[251,511,1673,1697]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trichotichnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="hamulipenis" subSpecies="nepalensis">
<emphasis box="[251,511,1673,1697]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">T. hamulipenis nepalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[516,582,1674,1698]" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">ssp. n.</emphasis>
(holotype). 98 &amp; 103, terminal lamella of aedeagus; 99, 100, 104 &amp; 105, median lobe of aedeagus; 101, gonocoxite; 102, laterotergite, gonosubcoxite, and gonocoxite. Dorsal (98, 100, 103 &amp; 105), lateral (99, 101 &amp; 104) and ventral (102) views. 
<emphasis box="[457,470,1746,1769]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">a</emphasis>
, apical spiny patch. Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm (98, 101–103), B = 1.0 mm (99, 100, 104 &amp; 105).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="341" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,1815,1878]" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1815,1841]" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[361,460,1816,1842]" captionStart="FIGURE 106" captionStartId="41.[151,250,1528,1552]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,183,1501]" captionTargetId="figure-19@41.[151,1435,181,1504]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 106. Trichotichnus hamulipenis sp. n. (nominotypical subspecies), distribution." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6781761" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6781761/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">Fig. 106</figureCitation>
). The nominotypical subspecies is known from northwestern 
<collectingRegion box="[1152,1238,1816,1842]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1253,1325,1816,1842]" name="China" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">China</collectingCountry>
), where it occurs at altitudes of 
<quantity box="[391,549,1852,1878]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.765" metricValueMax="2.13" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="40" pageNumber="341" unit="m" value="1765.0" valueMax="2130.0" valueMin="1400.0">1400–2130 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
